==English==
{{idiom2}}
'''in vain'''

#without [[success]]; ending in failure
#:''On the mountains of truth you can never climb '''in vain''': either you will reach a point higher up today, or you will be training your powers so that you will be able to climb higher tomorrow.'' — Friedrich Nietzsche
#in a [[disrespectful]] manner, especially when concerning religion
#:''A long and wicked life followed by five minutes of perfect grace gets you into Heaven. An equally long life of decent living and good works followed by one outburst of taking the name of the Lord '''in vain'''—then have a heart attack at that moment and be damned for eternity. Is that the system?''
#Using God’s name for profit. A fable. God told me to take your money. God gave me all this land.
#:''If you saw a river that had a natural damn, created by nature, one could say that God created it. As this word has an "n" after dam, then it should be OK to say "look at that God damned river".'' — Luby Benjamin

